Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operation with a nickel-scandia stabilized zirconia (Ni-ScSZ) cermet anode was carried out with liquid hydrocarbon of n-dodecane (C12H26), used as a model fuel of kerosene, without fuel dilution by inert carrier gas.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: Continuous operation was achieved for more than 120 h at S/C = 2.0 and at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: The obtained open circuit voltage was about -0.97 V and the average current density was about 140 mA cm(-2)
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: Under the constant anode potential of -0.75 V versus air.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: This current density corresponded to fuel utilization of 55%.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: In the impedance spectra for the anode, two semicircles were observed not only for hydrogen but also for C I to C 12 paraffin.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: Electrode conductivity for each semicircle, sigma(H) for high frequency part and 01 for low frequency part, were calculated by following equation: sigma (S cm(-2)) = 1/AR where A (cm(2)) is electrode area and R (Omega) is electrode resistance determined from each semicircle.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: Electrode conductivities for hydrocarbon fuels showed the same water partial pressure dependence as that for hydrogen whether fuel is diluted or not.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode

Sentencas: Hydrogen produced by reforming reaction was the most active element for electrochemical oxidation at the anode even for hydrocarbon fuels.
Titulo: Feasibility of liquid hydrocarbon fuels for SOFC with Ni-ScSZ anode
